Looking back at the `_parseNumber` method in the ReaderBasedJsonParser file, I noticed that the issue is at the end of the main parsing loop. After parsing the complete number (integer part, fractional part, exponential part), the code decrements the pointer with `--ptr` to push back the character that followed the number. However, it doesn't validate if that character is a valid separator.

